# Backlog Management Rules

Read `.claude/agents/backlog-manager/AGENT.md` before performing backlog
operations.

## Single backlog

All work items live in `docs/BACKLOG.md`. Humans own structure and priorities;
the backlog-manager workflow updates completion state (checkboxes, dates) and
the "Recently Completed" section.

## Rules

### After completing a task

1. Read `docs/BACKLOG.md`
2. Mark completed items: change `- [ ]` to `- [x]` with today's date
3. Update "Recently Completed" as appropriate
4. Prune "Recently Completed" — keep only the last 5–10 items

### When near-term work is thin

1. Point to the next unchecked items in phase order within `docs/BACKLOG.md`
2. Wait for human approval before adding new checklist lines

### What NOT to do

- Do NOT rewrite phases or narrative without explicit human instruction
- Do NOT add speculative items without approval
- Do NOT remove items unless completed or explicitly cancelled
- Do NOT reorder items — the human decides priority
